link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..39
mathematica: b[s_, t_] := b[s, t] = If[Length[s] < 1, 1, Sum[If[Mod[PrimeOmega[x], 2] == 1 - t && Length[Select[s, Mod[#, x] == 0 &]] == 1, b[s~Complement~{x}, 1 - t], 0], {x, s}]]; a[n_] := a[n] = Module[{l, m}, l = Sort[ FactorInteger[n], #1[[2]] > #2[[2]] &]; m = Product[Prime[i]^l[[i]][[2]], {i, 1, Length[l]}]; b[Divisors[m][[2 ;; -2]], Mod[PrimeOmega[m], 2]]]; A119846 = Reap[For[k = 1, k < 6000, k++, If[FreeQ[Array[a, k - 1], a[k]], Print[k, " ", a[k]]; Sow[a[k]]]]][[2, 1]] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 03 2016, after _Alois P. Heinz_ *)
